quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  10,107,"And if Allah touches you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>with harm, none can remove it except He; and if He wants good for you, none can repel His grace. He makes it reach whomever He wills of His servants, for He is the Oft-Forgiving, the Bestower of mercy."
  10,108,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “O mankind, surely the truth has come to you from your Lord, so whoever is guided—he is only guided to his own benefit, while whoever goes astray—he only goes astray to his own detriment; and in no way am I a trustee over you.”"
  10,109,"And follow<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>what is revealed to you, and be patient until Allah issues His judgment, for He is the Best of judges."
  11,1,"Alif Lām Ra. A Scripture whose signs{1}were perfected, then detailed, from One Who is All-Wise, All-Aware:",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is ayat (singular ayah). Ayah means ‘sign’ or ‘proof’. It is also used to denote the unit of text in the Qur’an, like ‘verse’ in poetry or ‘sentence’ in prose. Each such unit is considered a ‘sign’ from God.
  11,2,"that you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>shall worship none but Allah.<i class=""s"">(Say) </i>, “Indeed, I am to you from Him a warner and a herald of glad tidings."
  11,3,"So ask<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>your Lord for forgiveness then repent to Him, that He may grant you good enjoyment for a stated term and bestow His grace upon every graceful one. But if <span class=""h"">they{1} </span><span class=""h"">turn<sup foot_note=""80244"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>away, then I fear for you the punishment of a supreme day.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 2nd person to 3rd person.
  11,4,"To Allah is your return, and He is All-Powerful over everything.”"
  11,5,"Undoubtedly, they do bend their chests to hide from Him. Undoubtedly, even as they cover themselves with their clothes, He knows whatever they keep secret and whatever they make public; He is indeed All-Knowing of what lies within the chests."
